<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="554" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,258,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,258,283]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. First flagellomere blunt and rounded apically. Basal segment 
<number box="[992,1041,258,283]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554" value="0.25">0.25</number>
times as long as apical portion of arista (
<figureCitation box="[227,310,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[226,1342,576,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[226,1360,524,1991]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Hercostomus deltodontus sp. nov., male. 13. Antenna, scale bar = 0.2 mm; 14. Genitalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 15. Male cercus, scale bar = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: epn = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus, sur = surstylus, lat = epandrial lobe, pos = postgonite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226274/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 
<number box="[279,310,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cercus nearly flabellate (
<figureCitation box="[612,695,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[226,1342,576,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[226,1360,524,1991]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Hercostomus deltodontus sp. nov., male. 13. Antenna, scale bar = 0.2 mm; 14. Genitalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 15. Male cercus, scale bar = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: epn = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus, sur = surstylus, lat = epandrial lobe, pos = postgonite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226274/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 
<number box="[664,695,294,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus elongated, with 
<number box="[984,998,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554" value="1.0">1</number>
large and sharp dorsal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1414,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[226,1342,576,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[226,1360,524,1991]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Hercostomus deltodontus sp. nov., male. 13. Antenna, scale bar = 0.2 mm; 14. Genitalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 15. Male cercus, scale bar = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: epn = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus, sur = surstylus, lat = epandrial lobe, pos = postgonite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226274/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 
<number box="[1383,1414,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="554" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
