<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="556" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1466,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1610,1635]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[804,1040,1611,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xizangensis">
<emphasis box="[804,971,1611,1634]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">H. xizangensis</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
from Tibet of 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1289,1610,1635]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">China</collectingCountry>
, but may be separated from the latter by the large, sharp dorsal tooth on the phallus and short inner epandrial lobe of the epandrium. In 
<taxonomicName box="[325,494,1683,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xizangensis">
<emphasis box="[325,494,1683,1706]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">H. xizangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the phallus is somewhat folded near the apex, the inner epandrial lobe of the epandrium is quite long, nearly as long as the outer epandrial lobe (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[904,1044,1718,1743]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556" refString="Yang, D. (1996 a) New species of the genus Hercostomus Loew from Xizang (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 32 (4), 411 - 417." type="journal article" year="1996" yearSuffix="a">
Yang 
<number box="[971,1031,1718,1743]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556" value="1996.0">1996</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1128,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1466,1779]" box="[199,1128,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="556">Etymology</emphasis>
